Sentencas: The present work reports the electrochemical performance of the composites formed by SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta and Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta for their possible anode application in solid-oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Phase analysis reveals the absence of impurity phase on thermally treating the mixture at 950 degrees C in both oxidising and reducing conditions.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The DC-electrical conductivity of the dense composite sample is metallic in nature with the magnitude of similar to 42.2 S cm(-1) at 850 degrees C under reducing conditions.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode area-specific resistance is measured by performing two-probe impedance spectroscopy on symmetrical cells with Gd(0.1)Ce(0.9)O(2-delta )coated YSZ as an electrolyte from 700 degrees C to 850 degrees C. Porous electrodes with the compositions of xGd(0.1)Ce(0.9)O(2-delta)/SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta (where x is a wt. fraction of Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta with the value of 0, 0.5, 0.6, 0.7 and 0.8) are fabricated by blade-coating the ceramic slurries and subsequently sintering at 950 degrees C for 1 h in air.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The symmetrical cells with the composite electrode of 0.7Gd(0.1)Ce(0.9)O(2-delta)/SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta exhibit an extremely low electrode area-specific resistance of similar to 0.086 Omega cm(-2), which is nearly one-third of the magnitude shown by cells with pure SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta as electrodes at 850 degrees C in 3% H2O/H-2.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Introducing higher porosity-level in the optimised composite electrode further reduces this value to similar to 0.06 Omega cm(-2).
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, not much effect has been observed on increasing the pore-former amount above 30 wt% of the electrode material.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The overall activation energy for the polarisation resistance in 0.7Gd(0.1)Ce(0.9)O(2-delta)/SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta is in the range of 0.4-0.5 eV.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impedance analysis indicates that adding the electrolyte phase of Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta in SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta significantly enhances the kinetics of processes relating to the hydrogen-oxidation reaction occurring in the electrode.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The exceptional performance of the Ni-free ceramic composite electrodes developed in the present work without employing expensive and labour-intensive infiltration technique for fabrication highlights the exciting prospects of Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta/SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-delta composite as an anode material for SOFCs.
Titulo: High-performance SrFe0.1Mo0.9O3-δ -based composites for the anode application in solid oxide fuel cells
